# To Issues

Handle $ARGUMENTS.

Break a GDD, plan, or spec into independently grabbable vertical slices. Work
from the source artifact, not memory. If no source artifact exists, route to
`to-gdd`, `design`, or `grill-with-vision`.

## Source Order

1. User-named GDD/plan/spec.
2. Current conversation and active goal plan.
3. `VISION.md`.
4. Milestone map under `docs/milestones/**` when relevant.
5. Relevant World 1 / portal docs.
6. Current source/tests only when needed to make slices realistic.

## Output

Default output is local:

```txt
docs/issues/YYYY-MM-DD-<slug>-issues.md
```

Publish to GitHub only when the user explicitly asks. If publishing to GitHub,
read back the created items and record URLs/IDs in the plan.

## Readiness Triage

Before drafting slices, classify the source:

- `ready`: scope, acceptance, proof boundary, and sensitivity constraints are
  clear.
- `needs-design`: gameplay/visual/sensitivity design is unsettled.
- `needs-gdd`: no durable GDD/spec exists.
- `needs-grill`: product/learning goal is fuzzy.
- `needs-prefactor`: implementation is feasible but source shape makes every
  slice worse.

If not ready, route to the owner instead of manufacturing weak issues.

## Slice Rules

- Use vertical slices: each slice should deliver one demoable/provable behavior.
- Prefer a few chunky slices over many tiny guard/test/refactor crumbs.
- A slice can cross gameplay logic, Three.js scene code, HUD, state, tests, and
  browser proof when those layers deliver one behavior.
- UI-only work stays separate only when it is a coherent design/system pass,
  not one issue per button, label, or card.
- Fold test-only, proof-only, route-owner, and review-hardening work into the
  behavior slice it protects unless it is independently useful.
- Mark HITL only when human judgment, religious/sensitivity review, asset
  approval, or external access is genuinely needed.
- For Hira/sensitive content, every slice must carry the relevant sensitivity
  boundaries from the GDD.

## Local Issue Template

```md
## <Issue Title>

Type: AFK | HITL | Prefactor
Source: <GDD/spec path>
Milestone: <milestone map or None>
Blocked by: None | <dependency>

### What to build

Describe the end-to-end behavior this slice delivers.

### Player / product value

Why this is worth reviewing on its own.

### Acceptance criteria

- [ ] Observable criterion.
- [ ] Verification/proof criterion.

### Proof boundary

- Build/typecheck:
- Focused tests:
- Browser/canvas proof:
- Sensitivity/glyph proof:

### Non-goals

- What this slice must not change.

### HITL decision needed

Only for HITL slices.
```

## Consolidation Gate

Before finalizing:

- merge slices with the same actor/outcome/proof boundary;
- merge guard/test/proof-only work into the behavior slice;
- merge per-control UI tweaks into one system/design slice;
- keep a tiny issue only with a hard reason such as external approval,
  sensitivity isolation, risky migration, blocked dependency, or explicit user
  surgical scope;
- record why every kept slice is reviewable on its own.

## Done

`to-issues` is done when:

- the source artifact and `VISION.md` were read;
- every slice has acceptance criteria, proof boundary, non-goals, and AFK/HITL
  classification;
- sensitivity requirements are carried forward;
- local issue doc exists or GitHub publication/read-back is complete;
- active goal plan passes `check-complete.mjs` when applicable.
